  "response_text": "A warmly lit, old-fashioned sitting room or study is arranged with dark wood furniture, leather chairs, a fireplace mantel, framed pictures, a wall clock, and polished decorative objects. A middle-aged man in a dark, formal uniform stands near a low table; he has a neat moustache, slicked dark hair, shiny buttons down his jacket, and sergeant-style stripes on his sleeve. In the foreground, another middle-aged man is seen mostly in shadow from behind, facing him. The table between them is crowded with a tray, small dessert cups, spoons, and round pudding containers.\n\nThe uniformed man moves closer to the table as the suited man approaches. On the tray, several Cool ’n Creamy containers are displayed. The lids have bold lettering reading “Cool ’n Creamy,” with one clearly labelled “Dark Chocolate Flavored Pudding.” The containers are low, round tubs with pale rims; one is dark brown for chocolate, and another is a lighter tan or vanilla colour. Behind them sit small glass dessert dishes filled with pudding.\n\nThe two men stand close together. The suited man, dressed in a tan jacket with matching vest, white shirt, and dark tie, looks composed and slightly knowing. The uniformed man leans in beside him, his eyebrows arched and his moustached face intent, as if questioning him. The uniformed man’s expression grows more animated; he turns toward the suited man, speaking with wide eyes and a suspicious, investigative look. The suited man remains calm, glancing down toward the desserts.\n\nBoth men now stand over the tray. The suited man gestures toward the containers and cups while the uniformed man looks down, studying them. The display includes open pudding tubs, glass dishes, and small spoons arranged neatly on a silver tray. The suited man reaches toward the tray, indicating the dessert as though demonstrating evidence.\n\nA close view shows a spoon dipping into the dark chocolate pudding. The pudding is glossy and thick. As the spoon lifts, it carries a rounded mound that holds its shape, with a slow, creamy surface. Nearby, clear glass dessert cups hold more pudding, including a darker chocolate cup and a lighter, pale pudding cup. The lifted spoonful emphasizes the smooth, rich texture.\n\nBack at the table, the suited man continues to handle the desserts while the uniformed man watches. The uniformed man then takes a small glass cup and spoon. He raises the spoon to his mouth and tastes. The suited man bends slightly over the tray, still attending to the containers.\n\nIn profile, the uniformed man holds the glass dessert cup in one hand and the spoon in the other. After tasting, his expression changes noticeably: his eyes widen, his brows lift, and he pauses with the spoon raised, as if surprised by what he has discovered. He looks across the room and then upward, still holding the cup, his face shifting from suspicion to pleased realization. He continues to taste and consider the dessert, then lowers his gaze again with a more thoughtful, satisfied look.\n\nThe suited man is then shown holding a glass cup of pale pudding with a spoon poised over it. His eyes close briefly as if savoring the taste, and he smiles slightly. He looks down at the creamy dessert in his hand, then speaks while holding it up near his chest, presenting it confidently.\n\nThe commercial ends with the product arranged on a shiny silver tray: round Cool ’n Creamy tubs, including the dark chocolate one in front, a lighter-coloured tub behind it, and glass dishes filled with pudding. Large white text appears across the tray reading, “Too good to be pudding.”",
